JP8TLFY-1 01/30/2026 KMS (L)KMS 2026-606 SUB SB38
FISCAL RESPONSIBILITY AND ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT SUBSTITUTE TO
SB38
OFFERED BY SENATOR GIVHAN
1
2
3
4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing statutory law, the Governor may
6 remove from office and discharge from employment any
7 person who holds office or employment by virtue of
8 appointment by the incumbent Governor or any preceding
9 Governor except those employees subject to the Merit
10 System Act.
11 This bill would codify the existing authority of
12 the Governor under the Constitution of Alabama of 2022,
13 to remove from office or discharge from employment the
14 head of any state executive branch agency.
15 This bill would also provide that the removal
16 authority supplements, and shall not be construed to
17 diminish, the authority of any other official or entity
18 to appoint or remove such an agency head.
19
20
21 A BILL
22 TO BE ENTITLED
23 AN ACT
24
25 Relating to public officers and employees; to amend
26 Section 36-13-7, Code of Alabama 1975; to codify the removal
27 authority of the Governor without diminishing the appointment
28 or removal authority of any other official, board, commission,
Page 1

or removal authority of any other official, board, commission,
29 or other person or entity.
30 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
31 Section 1. Section 36-13-7 of the Code of Alabama 1975,
32 is amended to read as follows:
33 "§36-13-7
34 (a) The Governor is authorized and empowered to may
35 remove from office and or discharge from employment, with or
36 without cause, any person who holds office or employment in
37 any of the state executive departments and agencies branch
38 agency by virtue of appointment by the incumbent Governor or
39 any preceding Governor or by virtue of appointment by the
40 agency head, except those employees subject to the Merit
41 System provisions Act.
42 (b)(1) The Governor may remove from office or discharge
43 from employment the head of any state executive branch agency.
44 (2) This subsection codifies the existing removal
45 authority of the Governor under the Constitution of Alabama of
46 2022. The authority recognized in this subsection supplements,
47 and shall not be construed to diminish, the authority of any
48 other official, board, commission, or other person or entity
49 to appoint or remove such an agency head.
50 (3) Absent extraordinary circumstances, the Governor is
51 encouraged to consult with the agency head's appointing
52 authority or, in the case of a multi-member appointing
53 authority, to consult with the chair of the agency head's
54 appointing authority before removing an agency head from
55 office or discharging an agency head from employment."
56 Section 2. This act shall become effective immediately.
